Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.33,0:02:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I wanted to make a film...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.59,0:02:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... that would give the people who took LSD at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.34,0:03:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... the hallucinations that you get with that drug,\Nbut without hallucinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.51,0:03:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I did not want LSD to be taken,\NI wanted to fabricate the drug's effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.98,0:03:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This film was going to change the public's perceptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.03,0:03:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My ambition with Dune was tremendous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.75,0:03:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So, what I wanted was to create a prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.99,0:04:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You needed a touch of madness to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can't have a masterpiece without madness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.21,0:04:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Pink Floyd? Dali...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.25,0:04:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... or Orson Welles or others!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.29,0:05:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe Dune had too much madness?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.88,0:05:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But a movie that doesn't have a bit of madness...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.47,0:05:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,... is not going to conquer the whole world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.28,0:06:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think that in the history of cinema...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.99,0:06:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,... there was ever a film that was taken that far,\Nonly to end up not being made.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.37,0:06:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To become a different film,\Nsince a film was made...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.37,0:06:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,... that had nothing to do with those two and a half years of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.59,0:10:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was exposed to it in the\Nunderground cinema in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.46,0:10:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And after that, we had the courage to attempt to distribute it in France...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.80,0:10:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... and it was an incredible success for this movie that was quite revolutionary...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.56,0:10:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,... and a natural friendship was born between Alejandro and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.98,0:10:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to the success of El Topo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.94,0:10:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,... I got one million dollars to make The Holy Mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.37,0:11:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I did whatever I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.87,0:11:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I didn't have a producer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.16,0:11:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... no critic, no one to mess with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.71,0:11:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I did what I wanted and it was The Holy Mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.62,0:11:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I gave the movie to Michel Seydoux in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.41,0:11:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And, oh, surprise, in Europe it attracted a great number of people...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.38,0:11:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... it was playing openly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.09,0:12:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In Italy that year, it was the number two movie behind James Bond.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.93,0:12:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Holy Mountain was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.10,0:12:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So my ambition grew.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.82,0:13:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I have never made movies or transactions...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.86,0:13:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,... unless there was something more to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.95,0:13:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A relationship between human beings is what makes the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.76,0:13:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.09,0:13:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Because the book was the most beautiful science fiction book.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.64,0:13:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was the bible of science fiction for all the big devotees.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.10,0:13:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the book had been a worldwide publishing success...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.52,0:13:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... that you could find in every country.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.72,0:14:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hollywood sold us the rights for nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.72,0:14:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,... mockingly on the inside, I believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.64,0:14:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,... thinking that we would never be able to carry out such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.94,0:15:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was a great undertaking to do the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.61,0:15:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Michel Seydoux brought me to France.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.95,0:15:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He rented a castle, a huge castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.57,0:15:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... and I was in that castle dedicated solely to Dune.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.66,0:15:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Frank Herbert created a world in Dune...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,... but he never said exactly what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.09,0:15:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have a hundred pages of literature...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.76,0:15:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,... where you go on to discover,\Nwith great difficulty...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.64,0:15:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,... what the book is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.01,0:15:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very––  It's like––\NI compare it to Proust in French literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.48,0:15:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's literary, it's great literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.22,0:16:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He had the genius to make...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.05,0:16:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,... a storyboard with Moebius.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.84,0:29:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The first actor is the father, the Duke Leto.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.90,0:29:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}David Carradine had starred in a very popular television series...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.53,0:29:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,... in which he was a warrior...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.07,0:29:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... who was taught by masters from the Orient.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.16,0:29:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was influenced by El Topo.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.75,0:29:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, when Carradine knew that I wanted him, he came...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.13,0:30:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,... he came running.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.97,0:30:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I waited for him in Los Angeles, in a hotel room.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.14,0:30:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I had bought vitamin E.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.71,0:31:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened during a meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.01,0:31:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Pink Floyd?" Gibon said, "Okay, I'll go!"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.30,0:31:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He called Pink Floyd's agent.\NHe said, "Could I meet with you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.89,0:31:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So one day we went to London.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.48,0:31:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They were in the middle of finishing the mixing...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.86,0:31:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,... of Dark Side of the Moon,\Nat Abbey Road, the famous studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.86,0:31:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember, we got there...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.99,0:31:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,... and they were very standoffish...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.66,0:31:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,... pop stars, very distant.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.26,0:32:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, Jodo––\NWe called him Jodo.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.56,0:32:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Jodo said,\N"No. They're pissing me off. Let's go!"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.38,0:32:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that, it went very, very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.47,0:32:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Very, very well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.12,0:34:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Today you are 7 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.33,0:34:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you are a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.42,0:34:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Bury your first toy and your mother's picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.14,0:35:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When we started, he was 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.06,0:35:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There I trained him in karate,\Nkarate jujitsu, Japanese style.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.90,0:35:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all the fist-foot techniques...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.11,0:36:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,... joint locks, floor pins, standing pins...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.32,0:36:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,... a combination of karate, judo, aikido and atemi-jitsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.80,0:36:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I trained Brontis six hours a day,\Nseven days a week for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.57,0:38:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For me, science fiction was like a huge theater...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.07,0:38:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... like a huge work of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.87,0:38:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Every spaceship was a being...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.37,0:38:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,... like an insect, like a fabulous bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.43,0:38:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They were ships with souls, like beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.19,0:38:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It had to be Chris Foss.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.88,0:46:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Dali, to us, he seemed to be the only emperor of the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.21,0:46:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,... with that extraordinary talent,\Nwith his speech and his wording.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.66,0:46:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The first time we went to New York was with Michel Seydoux.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.58,0:46:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We went to the St. Regis because Michel Seydoux liked the St. Regis Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.25,0:46:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discovered that Dali was also at the St. Regis Hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.16,0:47:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The bar had a 6-meter long painting...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.45,0:47:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... pre-Rafaelite, where there was a king...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.58,0:47:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,... and the nobles had a face like they were hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.79,0:47:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Dali told me,\N"I like it here because there is a 6-meter painting...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.05,0:47:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,... dedicated to a fart."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.18,0:47:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dali told me,\N"We are going to see each other in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.64,0:47:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I am going to think about it."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.28,0:47:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In Paris, on the Champs Elysées,\Nthere was a very fancy restaurant...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.16,0:47:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... and he was there with his court.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.37,0:48:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He had 12––\NTwelve persons at the table and him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.61,0:49:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.32,0:49:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, Jodorowsky was part of the surrealist movement...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.08,0:49:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,... and Dali liked that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.71,0:49:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was a game between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.96,0:49:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would win the game?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.21,0:49:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He was going through his first adventure with Amanda Lear...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.80,0:49:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,... this sort of extraordinarily sexy person.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.26,0:49:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nobody ever knew if it was a man or a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.72,0:49:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... a completely incredible character.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.23,0:49:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A sort of muse, a poet's muse.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.79,0:50:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And you had to meet him, you had to tame him...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.75,0:50:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,... and he needed to tame you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.96,0:50:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So he would make you go through these initiations each time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.20,0:50:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She treated me very well...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.41,0:50:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,... and she became an ally...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.24,0:50:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,... because I promised her the role of Princess Irulan.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.01,0:51:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She said,\N"Be careful because Dali is destructive.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.06,0:51:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If he says 'yes', he is going to do everything to destroy the film."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.60,0:51:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Best paid actor in Hollywood.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.56,0:51:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I want $100,000 per hour."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.98,0:51:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I went back and told Alejandro,\N"We're never going to make it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.07,0:51:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't pay him "the most in the world."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.28,0:51:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.78,0:52:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then step by step...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.16,0:52:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,... because we were stubborn and because Alejandro would tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.74,0:52:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,... that Dali was the only one who could play the emperor...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.54,0:52:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,... the totalitarian emperor...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.37,0:52:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,... we had the idea of paying him...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.08,0:52:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,... by the minutes used.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.38,0:52:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I go to see Alejandro...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.05,0:52:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,... and ask,\N"How many minutes is he going to be filmed?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.76,0:52:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How many minutes will he be in the movie?"
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.76,0:52:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Alejandro says,\N"Maximum five, probably three."
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.76,0:52:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, "That's the idea!"
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.10,0:52:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I go back to see Dali and I say,\N"I will pay you $100,000 per minute!"
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.06,0:52:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, "That's brilliant!\NI will be the $100,000 a minute actor!"
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.73,0:54:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Paris was where Jodorowsky and Dan O'Bannon saw my work displayed...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.58,0:54:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,... and they wanted me to join them.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.34,0:54:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Giger had never done movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.72,0:54:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "You have to make movies."
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.05,0:54:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It was completely new to me and incredibly fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.41,0:54:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I met Jodorowsky for the first time in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.88,0:55:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the evening when he attended...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.97,0:55:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,... a Magma concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.29,0:55:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew nothing about the project, or the idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.75,0:55:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,... or the book for that matter.\NI learned about all of that afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.63,0:55:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Alejandro Jodorowsky didn't give us any direction on the music.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.97,0:55:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I believe he trusted us.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.43,0:55:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I had an idea because he had described the planet, the Harkonnen.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.39,0:56:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that they were not really the good guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.52,0:56:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,... that they were more like the bad guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.65,0:56:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was rather easy to imagine because...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.48,0:56:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... Magma made music that was rather violent...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.28,0:56:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... typically hard, things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.04,0:56:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just amazed by the quality...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.46,0:56:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,... and I told them I felt just like Christ when he was on the cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.76,0:56:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I was fulfilled, it was fascinating, the music.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.45,0:56:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I wanted Mick Jagger to play Feyd-Rautha, a character.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.16,0:57:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I going to contact this person...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.92,0:57:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,... who is not going to be impressed that I have the great power to make a movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.34,0:57:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He is in the peak of his fame, of his glory. How?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.89,0:57:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was invited to an event in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.06,0:57:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a big gathering of the Parisian bourgeoisie...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.89,0:57:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,... and at the other side of the room, a big room...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.23,0:57:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,... I don't know, maybe 150 square meters...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.57,0:57:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,... was Mick Jagger.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.90,0:57:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw him from a distance and I think he saw me...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.99,0:57:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,... and I saw him walking, he started walking––
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.16,0:57:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He started walking between the people...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.50,0:57:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,... and then I realized that he was coming to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.25,0:57:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He crossed the room and he stood in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.09,0:57:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And I told him, "I want you for my movie."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.76,0:57:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And he said only one word, "Yes."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.80,0:58:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was often invited to Andy Warhol's Factory...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.43,0:58:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,... Candy Darling, and all those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.94,0:58:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There I met Udo Kier,\Nwho was Andy Warhol's great actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.03,0:58:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He had played great roles,\Nand he said that he would act for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.39,1:00:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Orson Welles had a bad reputation...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.44,1:00:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,... because they said that he liked to drink and eat...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.86,1:00:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,... so much that he ate at the movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.07,1:00:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He ate a lot, and then he did not finish the movies, he was moody.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.37,1:00:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But I said, "No, Orson Welles is a genius, he is the one."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.83,1:00:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And since he liked to eat, they say he goes to the gastronomic restaurants in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.38,1:00:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Therefore, I sent a secretary to ask...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.76,1:00:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... in all the gastronomic restaurants in Paris:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.26,1:00:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"Where does Orson Welles eat?"
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.15,1:01:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the artworks from the movie...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.41,1:01:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,... which I got from Moebius, who drew the storyboard, where one can see...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.83,1:01:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... the Harkonnen Castle.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.75,1:02:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was fascinated by the creation of the Harkonnen people...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.01,1:02:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... and when I airbrushed five paintings...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.89,1:02:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... I gave my best to create these designs.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.82,1:03:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If attacked, then the spears would be set in motion and impale the people...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.57,1:03:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,... who stood in the way on the pathway up the castle.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.91,1:04:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact this Harkonnen fortress was never in the novel.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.84,1:04:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So this was somehow in Alejandro Jodorowsky's translation...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.35,1:04:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,... his interpretation of the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.44,1:07:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was such a beautiful object.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.61,1:08:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So well done and at the time,\Nthere were no photocopies.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.36,1:08:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was just photos of each drawing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.20,1:08:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In color...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.04,1:08:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... so well done...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.08,1:08:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,... with so much detail about the costumes,\Nabout the techniques used.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.18,1:08:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This approach was chosen precisely because...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.73,1:08:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,... I was thinking they might have a certain distrust of Jodorowsky.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.36,1:08:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But since we were showing the camera angles,\Nsince we explained each scene...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.28,1:08:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,... the way we wanted to film it...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.82,1:08:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,... they should have been relieved.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.41,1:08:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But they weren't. It wasn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.46,1:08:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In Los Angeles, I wasn't optimistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.88,1:09:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is that sometimes the French and the Americans...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.76,1:09:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,... have difficult relationships, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.85,1:09:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have had.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.93,1:09:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We were almost at the finish line,\Nbut we had to find the last $5 million.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.77,1:09:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The film cost $15 million.\NWell, we estimated it as $15...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.23,1:09:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We had been invited to Walt Disney studios by the chairman of the board.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.07,1:09:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He looked through the project and said:
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.28,1:09:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"This is a wonderful project...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.41,1:09:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,... but it is like the Concorde.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.58,1:09:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an exceptional plane, but over here, never!"
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.46,1:09:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And there I said to myself that we were going to face a lot of problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.45,1:10:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They always received us in a very friendly way...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.96,1:10:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... but it was always the same answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.34,1:10:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When we would give them the book,\Nthey were very impressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.21,1:10:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They had never seen anything like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.92,1:10:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Each time, they would tell us,\N"It's superb. It's very well constructed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.89,1:10:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You've solved the technical problems of those special effects.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.52,1:10:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's economically reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.27,1:10:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't get your director."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.53,1:10:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hollywood did not visualize science fiction that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.75,1:10:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was in 2001: A Space Odyssey...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.12,1:10:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,... or in small B movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.59,1:11:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But a huge movie, that would cost millions of dollars with all the effects.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.63,1:11:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not conceive of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.26,1:11:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was a bit long as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.76,1:11:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the film was a bit too long.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.77,1:11:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The totally outrageous side of Jodorowsky...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.06,1:12:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,... especially after The Holy Mountain and ElTopo...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.11,1:12:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,... did not give them faith that he could lead this very ambitious project.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.57,1:12:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Because $15 million in the middle of the '70s was a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.36,1:12:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was their answer, even though they found everything else to be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.74,1:12:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was great, except the director.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.29,1:12:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be like a poet.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.62,1:12:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Your movie must be just as you think of it and just as you want it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.38,1:12:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not take comments to change this or that from this person or the other. No!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.47,1:12:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The movie has to be just like I dream it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.28,1:14:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Very disappointed. Very disappointed because we all believed in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.61,1:14:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I believed in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.46,1:15:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is my take on it...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.67,1:15:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,... but I think he didn't feel like...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.09,1:15:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,... doing something else after such a project...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.09,1:15:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,... which was the project of his life, I believe.\NThat's my feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.43,1:15:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that the humiliation...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.89,1:15:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,... that Alejandro Jodorowsky suffered,\Nin not having been chosen...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.14,1:15:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,... in having been eliminated for being too original, being too surrealistic...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.32,1:15:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}... that is a permanent injury.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.86,1:15:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I think that Jodorowsky carries that in his heart for life.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.24,1:15:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was convinced that it would be something great.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.25,1:15:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But then Dino De Laurentiis' daughter...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.58,1:15:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,... came along and took the project away from us...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.76,1:15:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,... and gave it to David Lynch.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.73,1:17:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen the movie and I never will.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.87,1:19:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was a guide.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.28,1:19:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A guide for some.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.54,1:19:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, I am convinced that our storyboard...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.37,1:19:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,... made the rounds in the halls of Hollywood.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.21,1:19:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine that isn't the case.\NIt pleases me to imagine that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.75,1:19:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You always have to see the positive.